## Project Story

During my Data Analyst Internship at DecodeLabs, I had the opportunity to work on real-world datasets and experience the complete data analysis workflow. The project began with understanding the dataset and identifying data quality issues that could affect the accuracy of the analysis. I carefully examined the data, detected missing values, duplicate records, and inconsistencies, and performed data cleaning to ensure reliable results.

Once the data was prepared, I conducted Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to gain a deeper understanding of the dataset. By analyzing patterns, trends, distributions, and relationships between variables, I was able to uncover valuable insights hidden within the data. This stage helped me understand how raw data can be transformed into meaningful information that supports decision-making.

To communicate these insights effectively, I created various visualizations using Python libraries such as Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn. The dashboards and charts made complex data easier to interpret and allowed key findings to be presented in a clear and impactful manner. Through visualization, I learned how storytelling with data can help stakeholders quickly understand important business trends and outcomes.

This project not only enhanced my technical skills in data cleaning, analysis, and visualization but also improved my problem-solving, critical thinking, and analytical abilities. It provided valuable hands-on experience in working with data and strengthened my understanding of how data analytics is used to solve real-world problems. Overall, this internship was a significant step in my journey toward becoming a skilled Data Analyst and Data Science professional.
